{"cards":[{"lines":[{"type":"title","text":"Energy bands in a solid"},{"type":"headline","text":"Presence of many atoms broadens energy levels into bands"}]},{"lines":[{"type":"title","text":"Laser process"},{"type":"headline","text":"Electron moves to higher energy level"},{"type":"headline","text":"Electron returns to lower energy state"},{"type":"bullet","text":"Releases photon"}]}],"definitions":[],"secText":["  <b>Lesson:<\/b>  <b>    <br \/>  <\/b>1. Describe the energy levels of an atom using an <a class='pjumpToTopic' href='javascript:void(0)' data-chap='23' data-topic='2' data-subtopic='1' data-subsection='0'>energy diagram<\/a>.<br \/>2. Identify the energy band diagrams of <a class='pjumpToTopic' href='javascript:void(0)' data-chap='23' data-topic='2' data-subtopic='1' data-subsection='1'>insulators and conductors<\/a>.<br \/>3. Identify the energy band diagram of a <a class='pjumpToTopic' href='javascript:void(0)' data-chap='23' data-topic='2' data-subtopic='1' data-subsection='2'>semiconductor<\/a>. Compare and contrast the energy band diagrams of insulators, conductors, and semiconductors.<br \/>4. Describe <a class='pjumpToTopic' href='javascript:void(0)' data-chap='23' data-topic='2' data-subtopic='1' data-subsection='2'>doping<\/a> using energy band diagrams.<br \/>5. Define <a class='pjumpToTopic' href='javascript:void(0)' data-chap='23' data-topic='2' data-subtopic='1' data-subsection='2'>diodes<\/a>.<br \/>6. Identify the components of a <a class='pjumpToTopic' href='javascript:void(0)' data-chap='23' data-topic='2' data-subtopic='2' data-subsection='0'>transistor<\/a>.<br \/>7. Apply the concept of semiconductors to <a class='pjumpToTopic' href='javascript:void(0)' data-chap='23' data-topic='2' data-subtopic='2' data-subsection='1'>transistors<\/a>.<br \/>8. Apply the concept of semiconductors to <a class='pjumpToTopic' href='javascript:void(0)' data-chap='23' data-topic='2' data-subtopic='3' data-subsection='0'>photovoltaic cells<\/a>.<br \/>9. Define <a class='pjumpToTopic' href='javascript:void(0)' data-chap='23' data-topic='2' data-subtopic='3' data-subsection='0'>lasers<\/a>.<br \/>10. Describe how a <a class='pjumpToTopic' href='javascript:void(0)' data-chap='23' data-topic='2' data-subtopic='4' data-subsection='1'>laser works<\/a>.","  <b>Homework:<\/b>  <span class=\"KBInternalLink\"><a href=\"assign.html#OHW 23.03\">OHW 23.03<\/a><\/span>","  <b>Quick Review:<\/b>  <a class='pjumpToVideo' href='javascript:void(0)' data-video='true' data-vref='sum_quantum_semiconductor'>Insulators, Conductors, Semiconductors<\/a>, <a class='pjumpToVideo' href='javascript:void(0)' data-video='true' data-vref='sum_semiconductor_devices'>Semiconductor Devices<\/a>, <a class='pjumpToVideo' href='javascript:void(0)' data-video='true' data-vref='sum_lasers'>Lasers<\/a>"],"objNames":["wb_atom_energy_levels2","wb_laser3"]}